title: "cq-patient-data.ts"

## High-level description
The `CQPatientDataModel` class defines the data model for storing Carequality patient data in the database. It extends the `BaseModel` class and implements the `CQPatientData` interface.

## Code Structure
The `CQPatientDataModel` class is defined within the file and utilizes the `BaseModel` and `ModelSetup` symbols from an external file. It defines the structure and attributes of the Carequality patient data model.

## References
- `BaseModel`: Provides base attributes and model options for database models.
- `CQPatientData`: Defines the interface for Carequality patient data.

## Symbols
### `CQPatientDataModel`
#### Description
This class represents the data model for Carequality patient data stored in the database. It defines the structure of the data and how it is mapped to the database table.

#### Inputs
This class does not have explicit inputs.

#### Outputs
This class does not have explicit outputs.

#### Internal Logic
- `NAME`: A static property that defines the name of the database table associated with this model.
- `id`: A string representing the unique identifier of the patient data record.
- `cxId`: A string representing the customer ID associated with the patient data.
- `data`: A JSONB field that stores the actual Carequality patient data, which includes links and link demographics history.
- `setup`: A static method that defines the model structure and attributes using Sequelize. It specifies the data types, fields, and other options for each attribute.

## Side Effects
- Modifies the database schema by defining the `cq_patient_data` table.
- Creates a new table in the database if it doesn't exist.

## Dependencies
| Dependency | Purpose |
|:-----------|:--------|
| sequelize | Provides database interaction and ORM functionality. |
| DataTypes | Used to define data types for model attributes. |

## Error Handling
This code does not implement specific error handling beyond basic exception raising.
